As long as you win, we'll leave you alone.
"It was like a snowball effect", he told the police.
But the superiors knew everything, or rather, they suspected it.
"As I won, they pretended to close their eyes".
But then the start of the new year comes.
He loses a billion euros in one day.
In mid-January, after the weekend, he decides to hide the money.
On Monday, when he gets to work, he's no longer a bank employee.
A few days later, the bank announced that it had lost 5 billion euros because of him.
And how did we find out?
He became a suspect because of his leave.
"Last year I took only four days off.
