The national debt is the central government's debt and is mainly the result of the accumulation of deficits in the national budget.
The government debt is financed by Treasury bills, annuities, direct borrowing or, for example, by borrowing from the European Investment Bank.
The national debt of the State has so far this year increased from 38.5 billion to 719.4 billion kroner.
