The Congress approves the transposition of MiFID, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of the Congress on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the effort made by Members and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of bodies for the efficient functioning of markets.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, strengthening investor protection, enhancing the powers of the heads of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various heads of the European Union.
The new rules will allow financial advisory services to be provided for both specialised social reasons and to natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services (FSI), financial advisory firms (FAs), which merge with securities companies, stockbrokers and portfolio management companies.
It also increases the number of systems for executing transactions in financial instruments, so that multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems, which compete with current stock exchange managers, can be added to the regulated secondary markets.
The law also requires investment firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management and requires them to keep a register of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
The Committee on Economic Affairs of the Congress passed several amendments, one of which emphasizes that secured debt will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, as demonstrated by what happened with the debt of US subprime mortgages.
In addition, they took advantage of the transposition of the management took advantage to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after in 1977 was approved, the royal decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
The Senate, for its part, has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the ombudsman, who will work for a company, who will not require authorisation from the CNMV and who will be able to lend his services of marketing products and attracting new clients to different investment firms at the same time.
