But card issuers pay more attention to cash flow than to asset value, and so the fall in property prices has not necessarily led to a change in borrowers' credibility.
They could even bring benefits to credit issuers.
Consumer mortgage premiums fall if properties cost less than the value of the loan, so credit card debt would become a priority for paying it off.
Card issuers are able to respond much more quickly and with more flexibility to such crisis conditions than mortgage lenders, as they can change interest rates or alter credit limits.
This should in theory reduce the risk of a rapid stock recovery.
We're not going to wake up one morning and re-evaluate all the loans", said Gary Perlin, CEO of Capital One.
