About half of them were in court Wednesday for a failed 2003 coup attempt - among them Trillanes.
He took advantage of the audience to sneak out with about 30 supporters.
The military police, who were supposed to be watching them, had apparently deserted in his favor and joined his rebellion.
They broke into the Peninsula Hotel and demanded the removal of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Troops loyal to the government surrounded the area around the respectable hotel.
The President called an emergency meeting of the Security Cabinet.
The National Security Adviser Norberto Gonzales condemned the action of the soldiers.
"People are sick of it", Trillanes said.
"We call on people to join us".
General Danilo Lim, who previously commanded the elite Scout Rangers unit, said other army units would soon join the march.
