The two companies would however leave all options open, in particular to increase their stake in SA Freenet, it was learned.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet about a strategic partnership had ended in mid-October.
The still hard to predict Freenet poker game that has been going on for months is part of the consolidation of the German telecommunications market.
Freenet had 2.9 million customers under a mobile phone contract at the end of the third quarter and 1.27 million DSL customers and full subscriptions.
The United Internet and Drillisch Holding had until now a direct holding in Freenet of 6.01 per cent.
It was now agreed that Drillisch would bring in about four percent more.
The right to buy the 18.49 per cent stake in the investment company Vatas had already been decided in August.
